    <header>
        <h1>Simple Dessert Recipes</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Easy-to-make treats for any occasion</p>
    </header>
    
    <main>
        <div class="recipe">
            <h2>No-Bake Chocolate Oat Bars</h2>
            
            <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>1 cup butter</li>
                <li>1/2 cup packed brown sugar</li>
                <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
                <li>3 cups quick-cooking oats</li>
                <li>1 cup semisweet chocolate chips</li>
                <li>1/2 cup peanut butter</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Steps:</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Grease a 9x9 inch square pan.</li>
                <li>Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium heat.</li>
                <li>Stir in brown sugar and vanilla, then mix in the oats.</li>
                <li>Cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes.</li>
                <li>Press half of the mixture into the bottom of the prepared pan.</li>
                <li>Melt the chocolate chips and peanut butter in a small saucepan over low heat.</li>
                <li>Spread the chocolate mixture over the oat layer.</li>
                <li>Top with remaining oat mixture, pressing down gently.</li>
                <li>Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours or overnight.</li>
                <li>Cut into bars and serve.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        
        <div class="recipe">
            <h2>3-Ingredient Peanut Butter Cookies</h2>
            
            <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>1 cup peanut butter</li>
                <li>1 cup white sugar</li>
                <li>1 egg</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Steps:</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).</li>
                <li>Mix peanut butter, sugar, and egg together in a bowl until smooth.</li>
                <li>Roll mixture into small balls and place on a baking sheet.</li>
                <li>Flatten each ball with a fork, making a criss-cross pattern.</li>
                <li>Bake for 6 to 8 minutes until edges are golden.</li>
                <li>Let cool on the baking sheet for 2 minutes before transferring to a wire rack.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </main>
    
